  <p>System properties with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">jakarta.activation</code>/<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">javax.activation</code> prefix are deprecated and future
  Provides implementation of the <a href="https://jakarta.ee/specifications/activation/2.1/">Jakarta Activation 2.1 Specification</a>.
  The main jar file is now located at <a href="https://search.maven.org/search?q=g:org.eclipse.angus%20a:angus-activation">org.eclipse.angus:angus-activation</a>.</p>
  <p>As part of breaking tight integration between Jakarta Activation API
  and the implementation, implementation sources were moved to this new project -
  is published to the Maven repository and can be included in a project using
  this Maven dependency:</p>
                  &lt;groupId&gt;jakarta.activation&lt;/groupId&gt;
                  &lt;artifactId&gt;jakarta.activation-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                  &lt;scope&gt;runtime&lt;/scope&gt;
  <a href="https://search.maven.org/search?q=g:org.eclipse.angus">Maven Central</a>.</p>
  <h1 id="api-documentation"><a name="API_Documentation"></a>API Documentation</h1>
  <p>The Angus Activation API documentation is available
  <a href="https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/angus-activation/api/">here</a>.</p>
  <a href="https://jakarta.oss.sonatype.org/content/repositories/snapshots/com/sun/activation/jakarta.activation/2.0.0-SNAPSHOT/">here</a>.
  <p>You’ll need to add the following configuration to your Maven ~/.m2/settings.xml
  to be able to use these with Maven:</p>
              <a class="separator" href="https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/eclipse/angus/angus-activation/">Download</a>
              <a target="_self" href="api/">APIs</a>
